</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F00B841339687BE6FA58B588501FCDF6" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="type">
<paragraph id="F35B625718760981D74596D2738EF6E7" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C388F3421295D566BEFC8E41331CDEEC" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
ARGENTINA, Corrientes, 
<normalizedToken id="22F52C09BBEBF36DDCA0FF034DCF98A7" originalValue="Ituzaingó">Ituzaingo</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="B741593A17205E91CB94676C06C2F980" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Meyer</emphasis>
5786 (holotype LIL!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A624A4E18CA6DE04AD9C31740A8992C8" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="description">
<paragraph id="BDD21BE33042F344D7E83CB3E5ECB214" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9CA88015D90D40AC2F21CC12B65AD238" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
Densely pubescent or tomentose trailing or twining herb from a thickened rootstock, stems to at least 1 m long, relatively stout. Leaves petiolate, 2-7(-10) 
<normalizedToken id="4A02C79ECBDC45326A913F5E95C01724" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.7-2.8 cm, lanceolate-oblong with pronounced basal auricles, these sometimes lobed, apex acute and mucronate, margin entire to weakly undulate, base hastate; petioles 3-10(-15) mm. Flowers solitary (very rarely paired), axillary, pedunculate; peduncles 2-5 cm; bracteoles 2-5 mm, linear-lanceolate; pedicels 10-15 mm; outer sepals 10-13 
<normalizedToken id="16122B9B3F5053767E94C4A2B08955F5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-6.5 mm, elliptic, obtuse; corolla 2.5-4 cm long, white with dark centre, shallowly lobed, midpetaline bands pilose, extended into teeth; ovary glabrous, style glabrous, divided c. 16 mm above base, stigmas 2-3 mm, cylindrical. Capsule glabrous; seeds smooth to finely tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation id="5E45944CB423FEE73A4501D7175852B8" author="O'Donell, CA" journalOrPublisher="Lilloa" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="87 - 348" refId="B248" refString="O'Donell, CA, 1959. Convolvulaceas argentinas II. Lilloa 29: 87 - 348" title="Convolvulaceas argentinas II." volume="29" year="1959">
<normalizedToken id="8E695F18682194638AB796976C303798" originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
1959
</bibRefCitation>
: 285-288 (Figure 46)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DA60BB5FDC0C603F69D1E33255482A04" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="328BD52A048055836B4AC8DDD1E16E3B" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EFE66CA151CFE7B8A7403688A3C0BF33" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
Argentina: Corrientes and Misiones (
<emphasis id="5DF3E12C5962E2D4F828DDF584B679B9" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Pedersen</emphasis>
1912, 
<emphasis id="83ED74E5B731FF34608785E334B5E14B" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Ferraro</emphasis>
3094); Brazil: Rio Grande do Sul (
<emphasis id="1A66107D9A0D1097075BA84F91781AC1" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Lindeman et al.</emphasis>
8417, 
<emphasis id="1F181CCE272202C309C1DE91C556E7A1" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Ferreira</emphasis>
110). 0-500 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3516096E9B1A9525C12D9D5B19C98F15" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="notes">
<paragraph id="D3D3F6C09DB0D811F5D055BC2CAD46C2" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="63B9815A52B4676B14F2CB828135BAF6" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
An apparently very distinctive local endemic characterised by its large, usually solitary flowers and densely hairy indumentum. However, a number of specimens indicate that it is more variable than 
<normalizedToken id="C84FA81AA7E727944DF83C0CBA899CAF" originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
supposed. 
<emphasis id="CB2BDBBE51B73FE6EB5B54C1A81A0AE9" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Ibarrola</emphasis>
1305 from Corrientes probably fits but the sepals are only 9 mm long and the corolla a mere 2.5 cm in length. 
<emphasis id="9B463ABAD3F6D5289413C14F8486AB09" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<normalizedToken id="F0B37A1788BFB1124CB4FF1250A3B84F" originalValue="Dusén">Dusen</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
7310 and 
<emphasis id="FFAF17F7162FC070441BDC7085BA2490" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Smith &amp; Kiela</emphasis>
7814 from southern Brazil appear to be intermediate with 
<taxonomicName id="AF551C0FF4270570AF6564456DA9340F" authorityName="O'Donell, Lilloa 23: 430. 1950. (O'Donell" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Chodat" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hasslerianus" order="Solanales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hasslerianus">
<emphasis id="D13BF5742272F8925BD9D611077896D1" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Convolvulus hasslerianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the leaves are only very shortly petiolate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
